SIMPLE: self-sufficient
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-sufficient
<hw>Self`-suf*fi"cient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Sufficient for one's self without external aid or
cooperation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neglect of friends can never be proved rational till we prove the
person using it omnipotent and <qex>self-sufficient</qex>, and such as
can never need any mortal assistance.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having an overweening confidence in one's own
abilities or worth; hence, haughty; overbearing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧A rash and
<xex>self-sufficient</xex> manner.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>I.
Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-sufficing</ent>⟦br⟧
